# Axion — Dividing the Work: Minor vs Major

Here is the strategic split. 

The philosophy is simple: **Minor** must prove the core system works (data flows, twin updates, UI works). **Major** must prove the system is intelligent, robust, and enterprise-grade.

---

## 🏗️ MINOR PROJECT (6th Semester)
*Focus: Foundation, Data Pipeline, Basic Dashboard, Usability.*

**Fix the bugs and finish the foundation.** You don't need a heavy database or ML yet. Redis + Kafka + React is enough for the Minor, but the existing code must be fixed to be presentation-ready.

### 🔴 Must Fix for Minor (The "Broken" Stuff)
1. **Implement [temp_spike.py](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Simulator/scenarios/temp_spike.py) scenario**: It's currently an empty file. Evaluators will check your simulator.
2. **Fix [MqttMessageHandler](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Backend/ingestion/src/main/java/com/axion/ingestion/mqtt/MqttMessageHandler.java#10-32)**: Add `@Component` so MQTT actually works (crucial for showing "Dual Protocol" ingestion).
3. **Fix Health Thresholds**: The frontend turns red at score <60, but backend says <50. They must match. 
4. **Fix the Simulator Profile Bug**: Currently [fleet.yaml](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Simulator/config/fleet.yaml) profiles (sedan, truck) are ignored by [main.py](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Simulator/main.py). Make the simulator emit different base values depending on the vehicle profile.
5. **Fix the API UI gaps**: [OtaController](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Backend/ingestion/src/main/java/com/axion/ingestion/controller/OtaController.java#9-35) exists, but the UI OTA page is a placeholder. Add a simple "Trigger OTA" button on the Vehicle Details page to show it works.

### 🟡 Must Add for Minor (The "Scope Gaps")
1. **Vehicle-Level Telemetry Charts**: The scope explicitly demands this. Add Recharts line graphs to [VehicleDetail.tsx](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Frontend/src/components/vehicle/VehicleDetail.tsx) showing the last ~20 polling snapshots of speed, battery, and temp.
2. **Live Connectivity Indicator**: Show a pulsing green/red dot for Online/Offline, and show the "Last Updated" timestamp accurately.
3. **Logging**: Replace `System.out.println` with proper SLF4J logging (`@Slf4j`). An evaluator looking at your terminal output needs to see professional Spring Boot logs, not sysouts.

---

## 🧠 MAJOR PROJECT (7th Semester)
*Focus: Intelligence, Automation, Database Persistence, Enterprise Architecture.*

This is where you build the "Wow" features. You take the working foundation and make it production-ready.

### 1. Database & Persistence Architecture (The Platform Engine)
*Currently, Axion forgets everything when Redis restarts.*
* Add **PostgreSQL** for user roles, OTA campaign history, vehicle metadata, and digital twin policies.
* Add **TimescaleDB** (or just Postgres partitioning) to persist every raw telemetry event from Kafka.
> *Why:* This proves you know how to build a stateful, historical enterprise application.

### 2. ML-Based Predictive Analytics
* Add a **Python FastAPI Data Science Service**.
* Train a Scikit-Learn model on data generated by your simulator to predict battery degradation and time-to-critical-failure.
* Show the "Confidence Score" and "Predicted Failure Time" on the dashboard.
> *Why:* Evaluators love AI/ML. Adding a dedicated predictive service makes your architecture "smart".

### 3. Advanced OTA Orchestration UI & Logic
* Build a real **OTA Campaign Manager** UI.
* Implement **Canary Deployments** (select 5 specific vehicles to test update v2.0).
* Implement **Health-Gated Rollouts** (backend refuses to OTA a vehicle if battery < 20% or temp > 40C).
> *Why:* Shows complex asynchronous orchestration and business logic.

### 4. Enterprise Observability & Security
* Implement **Spring Security** with JWT tokens and Admin/Operator roles.
* Add an **Audit Log** UI screen showing who triggered which OTA event.
* Add **Prometheus + Grafana** (via Docker Compose) to monitor JVM memory, Kafka lag, and HTTP latency.
> *Why:* Transforms a "student project" into a system that looks like it belongs at AWS or Tesla.

### 5. Root Cause Analysis (RCA) Timeline
* Build a specific UI component that correlates timeline events.
* Example: *10:00 AM (OTA Started) -> 10:05 AM (Temp Spiked to 60C) -> 10:06 AM (Health Score dropped to CRITICAL)*.
> *Why:* Proves the value of historical data retention and event-driven architectures.

---

### Summary Checklist

**Do this now (Minor):**
- [ ] Fix simulator bugs (temp spike, profiles)
- [ ] Fix MQTT configuration
- [ ] Add basic Recharts to Vehicle Detail page
- [ ] Wire up the OTA Trigger button on the UI
- [ ] Add SLF4J Logging

**Save this for next semester (Major):**
- [ ] Postgres / TimescaleDB integration
- [ ] FastAPI Machine Learning service for predictions
- [ ] Advanced OTA UI (Campaigns, Canary)
- [ ] Spring Security / Auth
- [ ] Grafana Dashboards
